ate.json):**\\n- cron:ed2d0b5d — running, \\\"5p QLHV monitor\\\"\\n- cron:e7885813 — running, \\\"Agent Status to Lead\\\" (replaced previous)\\n- cron:6f3323ef — done, \\\"DTLX 5p Monitor\\\" (ended)\\n- telegram:group:-5163901258 — running but stale (~3h+)\\n- pipeline: HEALTHY\\n- blockers: []\\n\\n**Current cron jobs state:**\\n- 6f3323ef — enabled, lastRunStatus: ok, lastStatus: ok — this is the current running DTLX 5p monitor (me)\\n\\n\\n- ed2d0b5d — enabled, lastRunStatus: ok — running, \\\"5p Progress Report — AHV Works\\\"\\n- e7885813 — enabled, lastRunStatus: ok — running, \\\"Agent Status to Lead\\\"\\n\\nLooking at the pattern, the cron jobs all show ok status, but the sessions list appears empty. These are isolated cron sessions that started and completed quickly, so they were cleaned up. The key thing I'm noticing is that the telegram group session has been stale for over 3 hours now, which is worth investigating further.\\n\\nActually, comparing the previous heartbeat state where cron:6f3323ef was marked as done versus the current state where it's enabled and running, it looks like this is the same cron job being re-triggered as part of the regular 5-minute cycle. Both the \\\"5p QLHV monitor\\\" and \\\"Agent Status to Lead\\\" jobs are still running normally. There's no significant change to report, so I should stay silent. Both the \\\"5p QLHV monitor\\\" and \\\"Agent Status to Lead\\\" jobs are running normally without any new failures, and the previous DTLX monitor session ended as expected after completing its cycle. Everything's stable with no meaningful changes to report, so I'm staying silent.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Stable. No changes from last known state. All cron jobs running ok. Staying silent.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"