 Let me analyze all the sessions excluding the cron session that's running me (`cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e`).\n\nSessions to report (excluding this cron session):\n1. `cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` — \"Cron: 5p Progress Report\" (QLHV) — running, started at 1776195346099 (~3h 50m ago)\n2. `cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` — \"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\" — running, started at 1776199558073 (~1h 44m ago)\n\n\n3. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258` — \"QLHV group session\" — running, started at 1776163408296 (~14h 54m, but stale ~60m)\n4. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134` — done\n5. `agent:master-orchestrator:main` — done\n\nSo there are 3 active sessions besides my cron session running. Let me calculate the exact durations: the QLHV cron has been running for about 3 hours 51 minutes, the DTLX cron for roughly 1 hour 44 minutes, and the QLHV group session for nearly 15 hours though it looks like it's been idle for about an hour. Comparing this against the last status report from 21:34 UTC, I see the same three sessions were active then with similar durations, so the state hasn't changed. Since the task requires me to report regardless of changes, I'll compile the full status now."},{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll compile and send the report. There are 3 active sessions (excluding this cron session).\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uvrjzu7p9avj_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 21:44 UTC 14 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 3\n• cron:ed2d0b5d: running — 5p Progress Report (QLHV) — ~3h 51m\n• cron:6f3323ef: running — 5p Progress Report (DTLX) — ~1h 44m\n• telegram:group:-5163901258: running — QLHV group session — ~14h 54m (stale ~60m)\n\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Blockers: none\n\n— Orbis 🌐"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding",